{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "ce43ab65ddb1b1ae", "candidate": {"id": "cand-006", "name": "Fatima Al-Rashid", "raw_cv": "FATIMA AL-RASHID\nfatima.al-rashid@email.com | Cambridge, UK\n\nML ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nML engineer with 4 years of experience in applied computer vision for public sector and defence-adjacent applications. Active SC clearance. Proficient in Python and PyTorch with strong skills in model evaluation and experiment tracking.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nML Engineer \u2014 Frazer-Nash Consultancy, Bristol/Cambridge (2021\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained object detection models using PyTorch and YOLOv8 for CCTV analytics in transport infrastructure\n- Introduced MLflow tracking for all model experiments; led team adoption across 4 engineers\n- Performed model optimisation and ONNX export for deployment on edge devices\n- Collaborated with government client teams to define evaluation metrics and acceptance criteria\n\nGraduate ML Engineer \u2014 Satellite Applications Catapult, Harwell (2020\u20132021)\n- Developed image segmentation models for satellite imagery analysis\n- Built data pipelines for geospatial training data curation\n\nSKILLS\nPython, PyTorch, ONNX, MLflow, scikit-learn, OpenCV, NumPy, SQL (basic), Git, Docker\n\nEDUCATION\nMSc Artificial Intelligence \u2014 University of Edinburgh (2019\u20132020)\nBSc Mathematics \u2014 University of Warwick (2016\u20132019)\n\nCLEARANCE\nActive SC clearance (UK government)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (born UK)", "raw_linkedin": "ML engineer working on computer vision systems for public safety and transport infrastructure. Four years of experience building models that are deployed in the real world \u2014 not just on Kaggle. Active SC clearance. I'm a Cambridge local (moved back after university) and happy with hybrid working. Interested in roles where the ML work has genuine societal impact. Open to senior ML or applied research engineering roles, especially in defence, public sector, or infrastructure.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Fatima, tell me about the deployment experience you have.\n\nFatima: My main deployment work has been edge-focused \u2014 we take PyTorch models, export to ONNX, and deploy onto edge devices at transport hubs. I've done TensorRT optimisation a couple of times when latency was critical. I haven't done Kubernetes at scale but I'm comfortable with Docker.\n\nInterviewer: And your clearance?\n\nFatima: I hold active SC clearance. I haven't been through DV, but I understand DV can be sponsored through your MoD contracts. I'm willing to undergo that process.\n\nInterviewer: That's right, we can sponsor it. The 2-days-onsite model \u2014 does that work for you?\n\nFatima: Yes, I'm based in Cambridge so that's very convenient. I actually prefer having a couple of office days \u2014 I like the team environment.\n\nInterviewer: Are you interested in compressed hours?\n\nFatima: A four-day week would actually be wonderful if it's possible. I'm doing some part-time postgraduate study and it would help with scheduling.\n\nInterviewer: We can certainly explore that. Salary?\n\nFatima: I'm on \u00a368,000 at the moment. I'd be looking for \u00a375\u201380,000.", "years_experience": 4.0, "skills": ["Python", "PyTorch", "ONNX", "MLflow", "scikit-learn", "OpenCV", "NumPy", "SQL", "Git", "Docker", "TensorRT", "computer vision", "object detection", "image segmentation", "model optimization", "edge deployment"], "industries": ["defence", "public sector", "transport infrastructure", "government", "satellite imagery"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.82, "constraints": [{"id": "658f6bce", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "clearance", "description": "Holds active SC clearance (UK government); willing to undergo DV sponsorship", "canonical_key": "security_clearance", "value":